---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const updated = "June 20, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How Renderical collects, uses, and protects data.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:24px">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top:8px">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <p>This Privacy Policy explains how Renderical, Inc. (“Renderical”, “we”) collects, uses,
      and protects information when you use our notification infrastructure and MCP server. This
      page is a product template and not legal advice; consult counsel before publishing.</p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Account data</b> — name, email, and organization details you provide.</li>
        <li><b>Recipient & message data</b> — content and metadata you send through the platform on behalf of your end users.</li>
        <li><b>Connected accounts</b> — OAuth tokens and granted scopes for the providers you connect, stored encrypted.</li>
        <li><b>Usage & delivery logs</b> — delivery status, engagement events, and API request metadata.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To deliver, schedule, and route notifications across channels.</li>
        <li>To provide analytics, delivery tracking, and audit logs.</li>
        <li>To maintain security, prevent abuse, and enforce scope-based permissions.</li>
        <li>To operate, support, and improve the service.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Data processing & sub-processors</h2>
      <p>We act as a data processor for the recipient and message data you send. We use vetted
      sub-processors (e.g. cloud hosting and delivery providers) under a Data Processing Addendum.
      A current list is available on request.</p>

      <h2>Data retention & residency</h2>
      <p>Message content and logs are retained according to your plan and configuration, and can
      be redacted or deleted on request. Enterprise customers can select data residency regions.</p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>Subject to applicable law (including GDPR and CAN-SPAM), you and your end users may
      request access, correction, deletion, or export of personal data. Recipients can manage
      preferences and unsubscribe through the preference center.</p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>We employ encryption in transit and at rest, role-based access control, and PII
      redaction options. See our <a href="/security">Security page</a> for details.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this policy? Email <a href="mailto:privacy@renderical.com">privacy@renderical.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
